om-uuid","content":"Implied by which `isValid` matches: `uuidv4.isValid` accepts only version 4, `uuidv7.isValid` accepts only version 7."},"291":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-22","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-typeid-js","content":"`typeid-js` returns a TypeID object. uniku returns the canonical string directly."},"292":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-23","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-tsid-ts","content":"`tsid-ts` exposes a TSID object. uniku uses the native `bigint` as TSID's primary value."},"293":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-24","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-tsid-ts","content":"Convert at a string boundary when you need the canonical Base32 form:"},"294":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-25","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-tsid-ts","content":"Before replacing an existing generator, test the representation you store and expose. UUIDs, ULIDs, and ObjectIDs have canonical byte forms; Nanoid and CUID v2 are string-native."},"295":{"id":"/docs/migration/v1","page_id":"/docs/migration/v1","type":"page","content":"Migrate to uniku v1","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Migration"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/migration/v1"},"296":{"id":"/docs/migration/v1-0","page_id":"/docs/migration/v1","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/v1","content":"Prepare for the v1 entry-point contract without changing identifier data."},"297":{"id":"/docs/migration/v1-1","page_id":"/docs/migration/v1","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/migration/v1#move-cuid-v2-to-the-versioned-entry-point","content":"Move CUID v2 to the versioned entry point"},"298":{"id":"/docs/migration/v1-2","page_i